		<div id="comment_body_64588993"><p><div class="quote"><p>What thermodynamics breakthrough do they have?</p></div><p>I suspect the "breakthrough" is a white paper with some bad math.</p><p>This is just space based solar power by another name and the thermodynamics on space based solar is horrible, we have far better options on terra firma.</p><p>Elon Musk has been asked about space based solar power many times because of his association with solar power and rockets.  He's stated in interviews on how he's quite annoyed about these questions because it means having to explain again the horrible thermodynamics of space based solar power.<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

